results.definition: perceive by a physical sensation, e.g., coming from the skin or muscles
examples: She felt an object brushing her arm
She felt the heat when she got out of the car

results.definition: detect some circumstance or entity automatically
examples: This robot can sense the presence of people in the room

results.definition: become aware of not through the senses but instinctively

examples: I sensed the real meaning of his letter

results.definition: detected by instinct or inference rather than by recognized perceptual cues
examples: the felt presence of an intruder
a sensed presence in the room raised goosebumps on her arms
